":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"4676","uuid":"aef43404-30c3-4d7c-88b0-556229b88350","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 91E31B3111D1D1836BA5ECE6B45A3BC012B1C612\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit System - System Integrity failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254333","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254333","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254333","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254333r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254333","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent the display of slide shows on the lock screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> Prevent enabling lock screen slide show to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. \n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenSlideshow\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Slide shows that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel. Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged-on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6164","uuid":"6b408449-673f-4be8-a9dc-993cf698e905","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 533C4C8B637A166D851D795EDFDC46A9C4C3CB36\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent the display of slide shows on the lock screen.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254334","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254334","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254334","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254334r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254334","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have WDigest Authentication disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide . Set \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \" SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name:  UseLogonCredential\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain-text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS), exposing them to theft. WDigest is disabled by default in Windows Server 2022. This setting ensures this is enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2755","uuid":"fe24534e-340b-4658-ba80-2965536e64d6","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9A01716086030BF41118092F49BBCB47797ADDF1\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 must have WDigest Authentication disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254335","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254335","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254335","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254335r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254335","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing) to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3457","uuid":"aa660d0d-445c-4b51-a3a7-58953b15bfb0","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4E4714C570DB740AE5ED5F6CEC6492A4CF20F504\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent IP source routing.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254336","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254336","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254336","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254336r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254336","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing) to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8501","uuid":"45ef07b4-cca6-4912-a5d0-136096c6eba8","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C1E5D0ABCA3A3B87DDF6A327F6BD9DEE0113063\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254337","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254337","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254337","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254337r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254337","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly. When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via the shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6719","uuid":"87dcbc77-0894-445a-849b-2490d91d6494","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0769DD400F75F820A99644589430B6FF153F5EC1\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254338","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254338","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-254338r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-254338","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack. The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the server's WINS resolution capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"8991","uuid":"4853e51a-cebe-4d0d-b819-f9edf2e8f459","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C3B4C3EED75BA60781493E3C512DE46C1E8C757\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254339","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254339","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254339","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254339r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254339","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Lanman Workstation >> Enable insecure guest logons to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowInsecureGuestAuth\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Insecure guest logons allow unauthenticated access to shared folders. Shared resources on a system must require authentication to establish proper access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5055","uuid":"01de0aa4-e1fd-4002-a680-c7f0bfcc77c6","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9DD5D92515598FCA4697F49AB084DD01C52978F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254340","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254340","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254340","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254340r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254340","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Provider >> Hardened UNC Paths\" to \"Enabled\" with at least the following configured in \"Hardened UNC Paths\" (click the \"Show\" button to display):\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\NetworkProvider\\HardenedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nAdditional entries would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Additional security requirements are applied to UNC paths specified in hardened UNC paths before allowing access to them. This aids in preventing tampering with or spoofing of connections to these paths.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5787","uuid":"1e590f74-a487-4c7b-99be-7016b5886464","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 51CD23073A78584DC5A00363A5261144B8C5E801\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254341","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254341","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254341","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-254341r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-254341","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 command line data must be included in process creation events.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Audit Process Creation >> Include command line in process creation events to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\\\n\nValue Name: ProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling \"Include command line data for process creation events\" will record the command line information with the process creation events in the log. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"2962","uuid":"0f2f98b5-af46-4686-86ff-20aae0981354","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D2331AC045E2F42409B3192FC0DD3032DB511A94\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 command line data must be included in process creation events.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254342","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254342","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254342","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254342r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254342","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowProtectedCreds\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An exportable version of credentials is provided to remote hosts when using credential delegation which exposes them to theft on the remote host. Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard allow delegation of nonexportable credentials providing additional protection of the credentials. Enabling this configures the host to support Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5645","uuid":"53bf126f-57fe-4f13-b9b9-38a0685784b5","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 64583A4D78A8E6CCC606DC5EB2FD8031A97EEF41\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254343","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254343","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254343","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254343r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254343","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> Turn On Virtualization Based Security to \"Enabled\" with \"Secure Boot\" or \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" selected.\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"RequiredSecurityProperties\" does not include a value of \"2\" indicating \"Secure Boot\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"3\" will also be displayed in the results (e.g., \"{1, 2, 3}\").\n\nIf \"VirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus\" is not a value of \"2\" indicating \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Virtualization based security\" does not display \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Device Guard Required Security Properties\" does not display \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"DMA Protection\" will also be displayed (e.g., \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot, DMA Protection\").\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry values; however, due to hardware requirements, the registry values alone do not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nValue Name: RequirePlatformSecurityFeatures\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Secure Boot only) or 0x00000003 (3) (Secure Boot and DMA Protection)\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization Based Security (VBS) provides the platform for the additional security features Credential Guard and virtualization-based protection of code integrity. Secure Boot is the minimum security level, with DMA protection providing additional memory protection. DMA Protection requires a CPU that supports input/output memory management unit (IOMMU).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6836","uuid":"e22f4f1e-4015-4107-9299-559216ae858b","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E6AED855D7376B821CFE83FF4A54EFCCA73A773D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254344","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254344","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254344","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254344r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254344","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf this needs to be corrected or a more secure setting is desired, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Early Launch Antimalware >> Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy to \"Not Configured\" or \"Enabled\" with any option other than \"All\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0x00000007 (7)\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3), or 0x00000008 (8) (or if the Value Name does not exist)\n\nPossible values for this setting are:\n8 - Good only\n1 - Good and unknown\n3 - Good, unknown and bad but critical\n7 - All (which includes \"bad\" and would be a finding)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Compromised boot drivers can introduce malware prior to protection mechanisms that load after initialization. The Early Launch Antimalware driver can limit allowed drivers based on classifications determined by the malware protection application. At a minimum, drivers determined to be bad must not be allowed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4569","uuid":"2941b06a-30d7-49dd-9df0-c37dc2e9f912","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9DA07C6F8F1BD5774109A3BF6A45A6FB467138F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254345","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254345","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254345","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254345r1135378_rule","rule_id":"SV-254345","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Group Policy >> Configure registry policy processing to \"Enabled\" with the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is not applicable for Domain Controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\\\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Registry entries for group policy settings can potentially be changed from the required configuration. This could occur as part of troubleshooting or by a malicious process on a compromised system. Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3321","uuid":"c4b7c5de-a846-48bf-8b26-5335376d6b01","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 61D65E4F32C64C140AF5B817802E651C75878205\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254346","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254346","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254346","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254346r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254346","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system. \n\nThis setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8280","uuid":"389df7f4-b70c-4d69-96a2-a163ae301f7f","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 72985A442D372BDD95E700709714A85698E88231\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254347","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254347","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254347","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254347r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254347","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000160","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 printing over HTTP must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> Turn off printing over HTTP to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system.\n\nThis setting prevents the client computer from printing over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2441","uuid":"6206d4c1-c4be-4308-a63c-7bcbc7ca8137","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FB9EE822317B1596367D115FC6649C4CC1BC7115\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 printing over HTTP must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254348","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254348","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254348","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254348r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254348","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000170","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> Do not display network selection UI to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling interaction with the network selection UI allows users to change connections to available networks without signing in to Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8265","uuid":"34deb147-a353-4c74-9298-592bff94d912","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F0E49A2C0D6FC98E844E1F5A14FBEEC12951C671\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254349","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254349","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254349","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254349r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254349","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000180","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: DCSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8078","uuid":"320cbd1a-024b-48d9-8f27-52b31c8effc7","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5FE3191864E9CBA1E7A89864C30CC5A1770AF291\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254350","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254350","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254350","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254350r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254350","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000190","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: ACSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9578","uuid":"c941b859-84b3-47f6-a01d-bb3886d06bb5","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4D9A61E52DD00ACB5F3401F50B9A3022C44C5F3A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254351","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254351","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254351","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254351r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254351","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000200","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Application Compatibility >> Turn off Inventory Collector to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisableInventory\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system.\n\nThis setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5889","uuid":"9d484887-57ea-49af-b410-17d4aa4eb04d","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DEE889094316C6463E22F29DE85558D800215DCC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254352","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254352","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254352","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-254352r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-254352","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000210","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Autoplay must be turned off for nonvolume devices.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> Disallow Autoplay for nonvolume devices to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing AutoPlay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. AutoPlay begins reading from a drive as soon as media is inserted into the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. This setting will disable AutoPlay for nonvolume devices, such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"9836","uuid":"67efac86-baab-4912-819b-3424fef01fad","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 98B2C1C5DCCF00ED91225492D5428C70A67D63B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Autoplay must be turned off for nonvolume devices.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254353","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254353","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254353","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-254353r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-254353","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000220","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 default AutoRun behavior must be configured to prevent AutoRun commands.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> Set the default behavior for AutoRun to \"Enabled\" with \"Do not execute any autorun commands\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutorun\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing AutoRun commands to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. Configuring this setting prevents AutoRun commands from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"4806","uuid":"7daa0ece-2597-45a0-a83f-a6f121fa3956","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E820825E04F7232516911C2A078245395714902\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 default AutoRun behavior must be configured to prevent AutoRun commands.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254354","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254354","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254354","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-254354r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-254354","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000230","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 AutoPlay must be disabled for all drives.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> Turn off AutoPlay to \"Enabled\" with \"All Drives\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDriveTypeAutoRun\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000000ff (255)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing AutoPlay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. AutoPlay begins reading from a drive as soon media is inserted into the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. By default, AutoPlay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives. Enabling this policy disables AutoPlay on all drives.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"9376","uuid":"afb943cf-b688-4e94-9659-70f4e853ce1e","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E53F126D1135781CAC70087FB42EF3FE40E39EE7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 AutoPlay must be disabled for all drives.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254355","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254355","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254355","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254355r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254355","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000240","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Credential User Interface >> Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateAdministrators\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enumeration of administrator accounts when elevating can provide part of the logon information to an unauthorized user. This setting configures the system to always require users to type in a username and password to elevate a running application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6284","uuid":"c2699646-88e1-4a80-9461-eb9162694549","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 732C6D493DAA379764819A236C08875FE487DF95\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254356","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254356","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254356","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254356r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254356","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000250","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Diagnostic Data must be configured to send \"required diagnostic data\" or \"optional diagnostic data\".","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Build >> Allow Diagnostic Data to \"Enabled\" with \"Send required diagnostic data\" selected or \"Send optional diagnostic data\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"send required diagnostic data\" option for Allow Diagnostic Data configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender, and Diagnostic Data client settings. \"Optional Diagnostic Data\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3988","uuid":"023abc21-6fb2-4df0-a2ce-0aea3ba8adb2","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F2BB4FD2FD3EBE013AB7F0B74303D99D3A826BF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Diagnostic Data must be configured to send \"required diagnostic data\" or \"optional diagnostic data\".' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254357","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254357","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254357","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254357r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254357","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000260","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Delivery Optimization >> Download Mode to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\n\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nGroup (2)\nInternet (3)\nSimple (99)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Update can obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process; however, to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the internet must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5012","uuid":"1722cd44-32ae-47bf-a2b4-201b97fd6da1","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1360647615B780742D287BF275E7F7478A1F7DBF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254358","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254358","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254358","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-254358r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-254358","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000270","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Application >> Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"7768","uuid":"c02e137c-f438-4b75-8b5f-ac13023a06a1","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2FF5BE5399ABAABFCF214305A288B048E991831B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254359","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254359","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254359","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-254359r1186393_rule","rule_id":"SV-254359","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000280","rule_title":"The Windows Server 2022 security event log size must be configured to a value that holds at least one week's worth of audit records.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Security >> Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of a value that will contain one week of audit records or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is not applicable.\n\nThe registry configuration setting below must be set (at least) to a value equal to the size needed to contain one week's worth of audit records in the security event log. The value used below is an example that assumes a typical week\u2019s log size of 5GB.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nNote: The following registry entry is an example; the value must equal at least one week's worth of records.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue:0x49960800 (5120000) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel. System administrators (SAs) must monitor the volume of security event audit records and increase the registry value for the log size as needed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"7284","uuid":"713b1110-fd73-408f-b50f-42ad6f4108d2","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8FE192B9E53003AD078EC9117740B65E86D38D28\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Server 2022 security event log size must be configured to a value that holds at least one week's worth of audit records.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254360","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254360","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254360","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-254360r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-254360","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000290","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> System >> Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"9568","uuid":"9567a0af-b839-4463-a1b3-aee2a7c0628c","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 38930E7A658B72529800E09BB1EAE3709E39F4F3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254361","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254361","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254361","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254361r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254361","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000300","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen to \"Enabled\" with either option \"Warn\" or \"Warn and prevent bypass\" selected.\n\nWindows Server 2022 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Explorer.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems; for other systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the internet that may be malicious. Enabling SmartScreen can block potentially malicious programs or warn users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5196","uuid":"1115caca-e870-419f-b13d-4d62b5872e6e","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 49B5B6A0CA4C5A88D9F852FBB93DC85B35B9DFFE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254362","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254362","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254362","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","rule_id_src":"SV-254362r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-254362","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000310","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Data Execution Prevention to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention provides additional protection by performing checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running. This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"3613","uuid":"6e4e8fa0-5b35-4a66-bfbe-20798d12f966","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5E1517F4790BF93CC5A9A895F4DF9D4D78E923F3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254363","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254363","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254363","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254363r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254363","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000320","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be disabled.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Turn off heap termination on corruption to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt. Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8858","uuid":"a2131029-4c57-4bf9-9143-9a80b6f80786","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4FA4473F7A8F69E2939E9056884E63B904411D72\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254364","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254364","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254364","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254364r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254364","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Turn off shell protocol protected mode to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will limit the set of folders that applications can open when run in protected mode. Restricting files an application can open to a limited set of folders increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3335","uuid":"09a3ae82-f91b-4d77-90a3-09eb3ae08aac","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D8EB24DFA2A3DDCCD57A0A85C00AC77CEBED7B46\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254365","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254365","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254365","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254365r1051096_rule","rule_id":"SV-254365","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000340","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not save passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Connection Client >> Do not allow passwords to be saved to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system. The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"6359","uuid":"302d2a46-9fdb-4122-9541-4e38c6f13c28","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 00C5BB0462AFF55C3279C9B5A79B9D6B2451E8CB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must not save passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254366","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254366","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254366","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-254366r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-254366","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000350","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must prevent drive redirection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Device and Resource Redirection >> Do not allow drive redirection to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers with Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5162","uuid":"52bfe919-8645-4f01-916a-fd2da191cf0b","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5642561AF6F3F5B419A2EA560DE84FFE0F3C2D87\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must prevent drive redirection.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254367","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254367","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254367","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254367r1051097_rule","rule_id":"SV-254367","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000360","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> Always prompt for password upon connection to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection. Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"1382","uuid":"fb0fabf2-54f3-42b9-9acd-e984c9b23899","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 51CBA68130745C42EA12ECD17812F6C54B200604\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254368","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254368","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254368","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-254368r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-254368","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000370","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must require secure Remote Procedure Call (RPC) communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> Require secure RPC communication to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man-in-the-middle attacks and data disclosure attacks. A man-in-the-middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged. Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"9493","uuid":"fcde190e-5096-4782-ab15-3cfeda9c33b5","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 43BC2D7C6D97E5105A823940227524FB6EF940FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must require secure Remote Procedure Call (RPC) communications.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254369","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254369","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254369","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-254369r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-254369","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000380","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to High Level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> Set client connection encryption level to \"Enabled\" with \"High Level\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000003 (3)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"6528","uuid":"1db6825f-b883-47ed-b8be-fc41b58bb2fd","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D274E4403A595E0D71C87D8261A13D86EB72020B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to High Level.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254370","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254370","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254370","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254370r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254370","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000390","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> Prevent downloading of enclosures to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure. This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4612","uuid":"b644a131-b7e2-473c-b455-b05e1d37070e","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 28DE917FE1D958E57E5AADC4B6582E3DE0C88883\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254371","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254371","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254371","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254371r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254371","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000400","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3537","uuid":"10bd5ab4-6081-4f1f-b933-35e68d5d7149","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254372","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254372","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254372","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254372r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254372","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000410","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent Indexing of encrypted files.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Search >> Allow indexing of encrypted files to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name: AllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted files may expose sensitive data. This setting prevents encrypted files from being indexed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3762","uuid":"ee0fdbf7-6dd7-4839-bc16-2e59e087e394","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B10FB99818D7EE922183EEFC7C2992C0EA36CEC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent Indexing of encrypted files.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254373","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254373","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-254373r1051098_rule","rule_id":"SV-254373","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000420","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent users from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> Allow user control over installs to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators. This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8019","uuid":"8a174921-60ca-4ebd-bc5a-6fdfedc85e8c","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 60906CE61437D45568B78F893E755BD23428EA34\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent users from changing installation options.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254374","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254374","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-254374r1051099_rule","rule_id":"SV-254374","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000430","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable the Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> Always install with elevated privileges to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges. Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"5905","uuid":"328ca8f7-bae4-45e6-990e-5fff77b829e4","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C2DF52061544BC4B464C6DD53C06E0B3C1D59970\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must disable the Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254375","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254375","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254375r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254375","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000440","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system. Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7024","uuid":"4ed276f3-6125-4d3d-8704-53a17bf616b2","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3122A8E19C838522D1EB8E457F235E21E0DA12BB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254376","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254376","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","rule_id_src":"SV-254376r991591_rule","rule_id":"SV-254376","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000450","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Logon Options >> Sign-in and lock last interactive user automatically after a restart to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart. Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3307","uuid":"ec856dae-40f5-4d43-a006-0e40fe1e206f","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2ECD7D2F6799F14C6F217DF631FFC0BF4665702B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254377","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254377","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-254377r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-254377","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000460","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 PowerShell script block logging must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\\\n\nValue Name: EnableScriptBlockLogging\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell script block logging will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"7951","uuid":"5cac2b1d-1e3d-4a14-9183-5df51dea2de7","stig_uuid":"0d0f782a-92a5-488f-9189-ef7df4f274ba","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 646A6A55BB78E9C11DC7CB1C023FECC625040F01\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 PowerShell script block logging must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254378","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254378","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-254378r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-254378","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000470","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> Allow Basic authentication to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control